    {
      "text": "A man was found to be lying dead on the ground. His friend saw a snake passing in the area and took a picture of it and showed it to the doctor (image below). What is the most probable cause of death of this man?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Shock"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Respiratory failure"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Coagulopathy"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Renal failure"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: B) <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfad80a0f716927771979aae100f95\">Respiratory</span> failure</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The most probable <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"254dc5106d1692777183ba9ab1b3e5\">cause of death</span> in this scenario is <strong>respiratory failure, commonly associated with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3ebe379c231692777193c0afa683ed\">neurotoxic</span> snake venom.</strong></li>\n\t<li>The snake seen was likely an <strong>elapid (krait), which are <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3ebe379c231692777193c0afa683ed\">neurotoxic</span> species.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n<figure class=\"caption_element\"><img alt=\"Elapid (krait)\" data-author=\"Jayendrachiplunkar\" data-hash=\"13232\" data-license=\"CC BY-SA 3.0\" data-source=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_krait#/media/File:Bungarus_caerulus.jpg\" data-tags=\"May2025\" height=\"328\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/NtMrwE5ioZ5lqKc7dWSE1747983890.png\" width=\"500\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Neurotoxic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ce053080da169277720142dbefddb2\">venom</span> affects the nervous system, leading to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"72fa9105b916927771945aef35e8ed\">paralysis</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfad80a0f716927771979aae100f95\">respiratory</span> muscles (diaphragm).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Mechanism</strong>:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Neurotoxins block <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8b19cd5e161692777193ad958e52e0\">neuromuscular</span> transmission by inhibiting <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a79a62c36e169277718062f9630d56\">acetylcholine</span> at the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8b19cd5e161692777193ad958e52e0\">neuromuscular</span> junction.</li>\n\t<li>Leads to progressive muscle paralysis, including <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfad80a0f716927771979aae100f95\">respiratory</span> muscles, causing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cfad80a0f716927771979aae100f95\">respiratory</span> failure and death.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Shock (Option A): </strong>Typically seen in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"efbb05601b1692777202641ca3e610\">viper</span> bites (vasculotoxic) due to severe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9402185d4b1692777189cb62891ff1\">hypotension</span> and tissue damage.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Coagulopathy (Option C): </strong>Common in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"efbb05601b1692777202641ca3e610\">viper</span> bites causing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c6e0b26b8d1692777188ca8136898f\">hemotoxic</span> effects like <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"41e858bf2816927771836d46c619b9\">bleeding</span> and DIC.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Renal failure (Option D): </strong>Seen in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c6e0b26b8d1692777188ca8136898f\">hemotoxic</span> bites causing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4cdc8161f71692777180df58cafa93\">acute</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"98d387b7bd1692777201278b27be72\">tubular</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5e84a7987c16927771931012aced83\">necrosis</span> due to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ddeb334a351692777188795bb090ef\">hemoglobinuria</span> or myoglobinuria.</p>\n\n<p> </p>",
