      "text": "An alcoholic patient is admitted to the hospital 48 hours after his last drink. He presents with altered consciousness, disorientation, and severe agitation. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Delirium tremens"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Alcohol withdrawal symptoms"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Cocaine intoxication"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Korsakoff psychosis"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: A. Delirium tremens</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Based on the timing (48 hours), severe agitation, and altered mental status in this patient strongly point to <strong>Delirium tremens</strong> rather than simple alcohol withdrawal or other causes.</li>\n\t<li>Delirium tremens is the most severe manifestation of alcohol withdrawal, typically occurring 48–72 hours after the last drink. It presents with altered consciousness, disorientation, severe agitation, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bd1c98736616927771820954b0a744\">autonomic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2e780c7fd416927771895c61217c12\">hyperactivity</span> (tachycardia, hypertension, fever), and sometimes hallucinations.</li>\n\t<li>DT is a medical emergency with high mortality if untreated (5–15%). It is caused by CNS <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"774d8a439016927771890097e0854c\">hyperexcitability</span> due to the sudden removal of chronic ethanol’s <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"974aacc9c716927771867653a1dd71\">depressant</span> effect.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Management:</strong> ICU care, high-dose benzodiazepines, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b70d1dbde516927772000d7774d2a5\">thiamine</span> supplementation, and supportive measures.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Risk factors:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Prior severe withdrawal</li>\n\t<li>Concurrent illness</li>\n\t<li>Heavy, prolonged alcohol use.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Time since last drink</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Common features</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Severe complications</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>6–12 hrs</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Tremors, anxiety, insomnia, GI upset</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>—</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>12–24 hrs</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Visual/tactile hallucinations</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>—</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>24–48 hrs</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Seizures (generalized tonic-clonic)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>—</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>48–72 hrs</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Confusion, agitation, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bd1c98736616927771820954b0a744\">autonomic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"acb259200b16927771908888d1377c\">instability</span> → Delirium tremens</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Death if untreated</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Alcohol <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f5e32d045e16927772027c611a85e2\">withdrawal symptoms</span> (Option B):</strong> This is a broad term that includes all manifestations after cessation of alcohol; however, this patient’s severe <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2e9cc77ee216927771801bf1296c9c\">agitation</span> and altered consciousness indicate Delirium tremens, the most severe form, not just mild/moderate withdrawal.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Cocaine <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"fa5fbbb509169277719078b91cffd9\">intoxication</span> (Option C):</strong> Can cause <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2e9cc77ee216927771801bf1296c9c\">agitation</span> and confusion, but typically occurs during or shortly after use, not 48 <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"136c4bdd441692777189c5b2e976a0\">hrs</span> after stopping alcohol. Also accompanied by mydriasis, chest pain, hypertension, and arrhythmias.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Korsakoff <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1cb2d1482916927771964c2890313e\">psychosis</span> (Option D):</strong> A late <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8a6b09beac1692777184b08a2b5766\">complication</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b70d1dbde516927772000d7774d2a5\">thiamine</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> (often following untreated Wernicke encephalopathy) with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ee77d507701692777190bfcf47b497\">irreversible</span> anterograde/retrograde <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8078d5919c1692777181166124343a\">amnesia</span> and confabulation; it is chronic, not <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4cdc8161f71692777180df58cafa93\">acute</span> like DT.</p>",
